citeinfo.title: 2005 Natural Regions and Subregions of Alberta

descript.abstract: This dataset defines the ecological areas of Alberta known as the Natural Regions and Natural Subregions, as defined in 2004/2005. The intended scale of use of this product is 1:250 000. This version is 2005 Final. Note that the Athabasca Plain subregion has been moved into the Boreal Natural Region and that the Boreal Highlands has now been split into Lower and Upper. Linework changes from the previous Natural Subregion delineation are due both to better information and refined subregion definitions. There is an accompanying report, published 2006. Update, June 2016: These data have been rectified to Alberta Township Survey (ATS) 4.1, using a "dissolve" of the Seed Zones of Alberta polygons (already rectified to ATS 4.1), by Natural Subregion Name. No polygon values were changed in this process; however, line work of some polygons along the provincial boundary has been adjusted slightly, for agreement with the ATS 4.1 provincial boundary polygon. The number of Alpine subregion polygons has decreased from 276 to 274 as a result of these minor adjustments.
descript.purpose: This dataset is intended to allow for the stratification of the province of Alberta based on ecological criteria. This dataset should be used in conjunction with the related final report.

procstep.procdesc: 1. Source information was plotted out at 1:250 000 scale on NTS mapsheet tiles. 2. Linework was drafted onto clear film overlays. 3. Film was photocopied onto paper. 4. Hardcopy linework was digitized using ArcInfo 7.2.1. 5. Linework was cleaned up using ArcInfo 7.2.1. 6. Attribute fields were added in ArcInfo 7.2.1. 7. Attribute population and cleanup was done using ArcView 3.2. 8. Sliver removal in ArcEdit 7.2.1. 9. Update, June 2016: The Seed Zones of Alberta dataset, which contains Natural Subregions and whose internal polygons were rectified to the Natural Regions 2005 data, and which was rectified along the Alberta Provincial Boundary to ATS 4.1, was used as the source data to achieve Natural Subregions data rectified to ATS 4.1, via a dissolve on Natural Subregion Name. Polygons were checked against the original 2005 Natural Subregions data, via Symmetrical Difference and Union overlays with the 2005 Natural Subregions data. Internal polygons were found to be accurate - only polygons adjacent to the Alberta boundary differed from the 2005 data, due to minor adjustments to rectify boundary polygons to the ATS 4.1 provincial boundary.

srcinfo.srccontr: The Base Features Geoadministrative Areas ATS v4.1 Alberta Provincial Boundary defines the boundary for the Province of Alberta. It was used to standardize both the Seed Zones of Alberta and the 2005 Natural Regions and Subregions of Alberta.

procstep.procdesc: The Seed Zones of Alberta feature class was loaded into a feature dataset with the ATS v4.1 Alberta Provincial Boundary feature class and the 2005 Natural Regions and Subregions of Alberta feature class. The following processes were run: 1. Both the 2005 Natural Regions and Subregions of Alberta and the Seed Zones of Alberta were clipped to the provincial boundary. 2. The Integrate command was run using tolerances of .005, .01 and .05 metres. The ATS v4.1 Alberta Provincial Boundary was ranked as 1, the 2005 Natural Regions and Subregions of Alberta was ranked as 2 and the Seed Zones of Alberta was ranked as 3. 3. The remaining gaps and inconsistencies were identified using topological rules and corrected manually.
